CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1952, pg. 11 reads: "Presents NCNW Book - Mrs. Eunice W. Cook presented the national Council of Negro Women's Book, "Women United," to Mrs. Anne Eberhard, German woman broadcaster, who has been visiting this country. Mrs. Eberhard was interested in hearing about the council as she is one of the directors of the Frankfurt (Germany) Women's Club. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Eunice Cook wearing hat and jacket with studded collar and cuffs, presenting book titled "Women United Souvenir Yearbook Sixteenth Anniversary, National Council of Negro Women, Inc." to Anne Eberhard, seated on love seat in interior
